ut there is something challenging about introducing a collection of arguments meant to speak for themselves. It still bears the stamp of a fantastic mind, and still has its shining moments.","rating":5,"shelving":{"__typename":"Shelving","shelf":{"__typename":"Shelf","name":"read","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/1360306?shelf=read"},"taggings":[],"webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/33792364"},"likeCount":34,"viewerHasLiked":null,"commentCount":3,"viewerCanComment({\"resourceType\":\"review\"})":null},"User:16897950":{"id":16897950,"__typename":"User","legacyId":16897950,"imageUrlSquare":"https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1359554258i/16897950._UX200_CR0,62,200,200_.jpg","isAuthor":false,"textReviewsCount":486,"viewableName":"Tiffany","isBlockedByViewer":false,"webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/user/show/16897950-tiffany","contributor":null,"isFollowing":false,"isFriend":false,"followersCount":0},"Review:kca://review:goodreads/amzn1.gr.review:goodreads.v1.BhqmLFLNMKJa0v_sF3__DQ":{"id":"kca://review:goodreads/amzn1.gr.review:goodreads.v1.BhqmLFLNMKJa0v_sF3__DQ","__typename":"Review","book":{"__ref":"Book:kca://book/amzn1.gr.book.v1.IvZ-sB10MCL9VD9sHdLPZA"},"creator":{"__ref":"User:16897950"},"recommendFor":null,"updatedAt":1632512419396,"createdAt":1359430114000,"spoilerStatus":false,"lastRevisionAt":1470873881412,"text":"Loved the guy. He lived in my neighborhood and lumbered around like a bear that had been poked by a stick. I've been following him since the 80's when he contributed regularly to The Nation. His contributions to Vanity Fair, The Atlantic, Foreign Policy and Prospect were invaluable, his prose inimitable.\u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eBut when it comes to spiritual beliefs the guy was a cretin.\u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eFor all his erudition he never grokked that many humans have a desire to worship something outside themselves and that desire or need does not automatically make them stupid, deluded, evil or dangerous.\u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eThat was always Chris' problem: people's needs and weaknesses constituted a target for his rage. Once, in the early 90's at a briefing at Chapters Bookstore during the Serbian conflict he YELLED at some poor guy asking for some clarification on who was who. And I mean full-on Christian Bale. I got quiet and slipped out the door fearing he would become insane and kill someone. His righteous anger turned him into an enraged and senseless animal. This just to tell you he had no understanding or observation of his personal failings, which is why he drank and smoked himself (sadly) into an early grave. \u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eThat said, he was the closest thing to a wit and an intellectual we've had in the US.","rating":3,"shelving":{"__typename":"Shelving","shelf":{"__typename":"Shelf","name":"read","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/16897950?shelf=read"},"taggings":[{"__typename":"Tagging","tag":{"__typename":"Tag","name":"metaphysical","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/16897950?shelf=metaphysical"}}],"webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/520189694"},"likeCount":24,"viewerHasLiked":null,"commentCount":17,"viewerCanComment({\"resourceType\":\"review\"})":null},"Contributor:kca://author/amzn1.gr.author.v1.XMux0k7jVsyME5lhXXKlvA":{"id":"kca://author/amzn1.gr.author.v1.XMux0k7jVsyME5lhXXKlvA","__typename":"Contributor","works":{"__typename":"ContributorWorksConnection","totalCount":6}},"User:266149":{"id":266149,"__typename":"User","legacyId":266149,"imageUrlSquare":"https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1537964051i/266149._UX200_CR0,0,200,200_.jpg","isAuthor":true,"textReviewsCount":326,"viewableName":"Michael","isBlockedByViewer":false,"webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/user/show/266149-michael","contributor":{"__ref":"Contributor:kca://author/amzn1.gr.author.v1.XMux0k7jVsyME5lhXXKlvA"},"isFollowing":false,"isFriend":false,"fo